1
00:01:02,058 --> 00:01:03,183
Yan!

2
00:01:03,892 --> 00:01:06,142
That's enough! Stop!

3
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:09,267
Stop it!

4
00:01:26,017 --> 00:01:31,600
MAY 2002
SIX MONTHS BEFORE YAN'S DEATH

5
00:01:39,225 --> 00:01:41,433
Do you know what "messed up" means?

6
00:01:41,683 --> 00:01:46,766
The first masseuse that came in
looked exactly like Sam's dog

7
00:01:47,016 --> 00:01:49,141
so I asked for a replacement.

8
00:01:49,391 --> 00:01:52,100
The next one that came in
was even worse.

9
00:01:52,350 --> 00:01:54,308
She looked identical to Sam.

10
00:01:54,558 --> 00:01:58,266
Can you imagine?
Even I couldn't handle that.

11
00:01:58,558 --> 00:02:02,725
She had the audacity to ask me if she
was pretty. Of course I said no.

12
00:02:02,975 --> 00:02:04,558
Then she clawed me.

13
00:02:04,808 --> 00:02:05,975
So I called you.

14
00:02:06,225 --> 00:02:07,516
That's when we messed up.

15
00:02:07,766 --> 00:02:11,391
You smashed the whole place up.
It'll cost me a fortune in damages.

16
00:02:11,641 --> 00:02:14,808
So if a masseuse is ugly,
you're definitely screwed.

17
00:02:18,433 --> 00:02:21,308
Why are you swearing at your boss?

18
00:02:22,683 --> 00:02:25,058
Nurse, it's not sore, is it?

19
00:02:26,475 --> 00:02:27,641
Yan...

20
00:02:28,516 --> 00:02:31,641
I asked you to do a small job.
You don't have to be like that.

21
00:02:32,516 --> 00:02:35,558
You moan
that I don't give you anything to do.

22
00:02:35,808 --> 00:02:38,183
You don't need to work
in this business.

23
00:02:38,433 --> 00:02:41,141
If you want to work,
why don't you go and be a cop?

24
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:46,558
Do you know why
I've only got you under my wing?

25
00:02:47,308 --> 00:02:50,266
It's because
I like that you're focused.

26
00:02:50,516 --> 00:02:52,308
It's important to be focused.

27
00:02:52,558 --> 00:02:55,058
Look at Sam. He's focused, isn't he?

28
00:02:55,308 --> 00:02:57,725
As for what happened today...

29
00:02:57,975 --> 00:02:59,558
Don't let Sam know.

30
00:02:59,808 --> 00:03:03,766
Ever since his wife died, he hates us
going to massage parlours.

31
00:03:04,350 --> 00:03:05,766
Why don't you let me go?

32
00:03:06,016 --> 00:03:07,850
Are you done talking? Get inside.

33
00:03:08,100 --> 00:03:10,350
Hey, don't push me, Officer.

34
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:12,141
That's not the way to behave.

35
00:03:12,391 --> 00:03:14,433
Even cops shouldn't be like that.

36
00:03:15,141 --> 00:03:17,391
So are you going to tell on me?

37
00:03:17,641 --> 00:03:18,600
That's enough.

38
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:23,225
That's life. Either you get me or I get you.
Are you going to tell on me?

39
00:03:23,475 --> 00:03:25,016
- Fuck off!
- Don't fight!

40
00:03:25,266 --> 00:03:26,891
You're hitting your own boss?

41
00:04:55,725 --> 00:05:00,600
OCTOBER 2003
TEN MONTHS AFTER YAN'S DEATH

42
00:05:00,850 --> 00:05:03,058
File number IO143 -

43
00:05:03,308 --> 00:05:06,766
regarding the deaths of 27149,
Officer Chan Wing Yan

44
00:05:07,016 --> 00:05:11,100
and 34689, Officer Lam Gok Ping.

45
00:05:11,766 --> 00:05:15,224
Internal Affairs
have produced the following report.

46
00:05:15,474 --> 00:05:17,974
On November 26th 2002,

47
00:05:18,266 --> 00:05:20,016
Senior Inspector Lau Kin Ming of IA

48
00:05:20,308 --> 00:05:23,891
contacted undercover officer,
Chan Wing Yan.

49
00:05:24,141 --> 00:05:27,183
With help from Officer Chan

50
00:05:27,433 --> 00:05:31,224
and from the OCTB unit
in West Kowloon,

51
00:05:31,474 --> 00:05:33,558
Lau toppled Sam's drug operation

52
00:05:33,808 --> 00:05:37,641
and cocaine
worth HK$60 million was seized.

53
00:05:37,891 --> 00:05:40,266
On November 27th 2002,

54
00:05:40,516 --> 00:05:43,474
Officer Chan met with Inspector Lau,

55
00:05:43,724 --> 00:05:45,933
on the rooftop
of the Sei Fong Centre.

56
00:05:46,224 --> 00:05:48,766
Yan supplied information
on triad moles.

57
00:05:51,141 --> 00:05:52,724
You can't get away.

58
00:05:52,974 --> 00:05:53,974
Just wait and see.

59
00:05:56,724 --> 00:05:58,349
You're going to kill a cop?

60
00:06:02,641 --> 00:06:05,474
I know all about you and Sam.

61
00:06:05,724 --> 00:06:08,016
You have no choice.
Come back with me.

62
00:06:08,308 --> 00:06:09,308
Drop your gun.

63
00:06:14,641 --> 00:06:16,683
- What do you want?
- I want to get away.

64
00:06:29,391 --> 00:06:33,849
The preceding testimony was provided
by Senior Inspector Lau Kin Ming.

65
00:06:34,099 --> 00:06:36,516
The committee
of two Chief Superintendents

66
00:06:37,016 --> 00:06:39,016
and the Assistant Commissioner

67
00:06:39,308 --> 00:06:41,641
unanimously believe Lau's testimony.

68
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:45,016
Inspector Lau's killing

69
00:06:45,308 --> 00:06:49,391
of Officer Lam Kok Ping
has been ruled legal.

70
00:06:49,891 --> 00:06:54,933
Lam has been confirmed as a mole
sent by Sam into the police force.

71
00:06:55,641 --> 00:06:57,183
Finally, it's all over.

72
00:07:00,599 --> 00:07:01,724
You all believe me?

73
00:07:01,974 --> 00:07:03,433
It's all over.

74
00:07:04,474 --> 00:07:06,016
Stay in Admin for now, OK?

75
00:07:08,766 --> 00:07:09,808
Wait.

76
00:07:11,641 --> 00:07:12,641
Got it.

77
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:15,724
Your parking space -
wait three weeks. That's it.

78
00:07:16,516 --> 00:07:17,474
Bye.

79
00:07:18,391 --> 00:07:19,808
Officer Chan.

80
00:07:20,099 --> 00:07:21,849
Hold on.

81
00:07:23,224 --> 00:07:26,099
Your uniform's ready.
Come and get it if you're free.

82
00:07:26,349 --> 00:07:28,183
Or I can send it over to you.

83
00:07:29,141 --> 00:07:31,474
No problem! OK. Bye.

84
00:07:31,724 --> 00:07:34,183
It's a shame Lam destroyed the CCTV.

85
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:36,224
It's dragged on for so long.

86
00:07:36,474 --> 00:07:39,058
You know
our bosses go on accountability.

87
00:07:39,308 --> 00:07:42,349
Luckily, you're one of us.
It was all sorted quickly.

88
00:07:43,224 --> 00:07:45,141
You can come back to IA next month.

89
00:07:45,933 --> 00:07:47,224
Are you tired?

90
00:07:47,474 --> 00:07:49,933
If you are, you should go
on holiday with Mary.

91
00:07:51,016 --> 00:07:52,099
Hello.

92
00:08:02,474 --> 00:08:03,433
OK.

93
00:08:06,266 --> 00:08:08,099
I'll sign the documents tomorrow.

94
00:08:10,183 --> 00:08:11,141
OK.

95
00:08:12,308 --> 00:08:13,683
We can split it.

96
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:16,516
We can split it.

97
00:08:21,349 --> 00:08:23,224
We can split anything but the baby!

98
00:08:33,224 --> 00:08:34,516
Hello, Officer Chan,

99
00:08:35,766 --> 00:08:36,933
your uniform's ready.

100
00:08:37,183 --> 00:08:39,391
If you're busy, I can send it over.

101
00:08:40,266 --> 00:08:43,266
I can do it. OK, wait for me. Bye.

102
00:09:28,849 --> 00:09:30,724
Have I done something wrong?

103
00:09:34,016 --> 00:09:35,974
I feel like beating someone up today.

104
00:09:40,932 --> 00:09:43,557
What's with all the fuss,
Superintendent Yeung?

105
00:09:47,432 --> 00:09:50,349
These Taiwanese men are arms dealers.

106
00:09:51,432 --> 00:09:54,099
Their customers haven't shown up.

107
00:09:55,682 --> 00:09:58,349
They seemed bored,
so I'm keeping them company.

108
00:09:58,974 --> 00:09:59,932
OK?

109
00:10:00,224 --> 00:10:01,557
Sure.

110
00:10:04,391 --> 00:10:05,807
I work in the Security Wing.

111
00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:10,641
I don't like to see
respectable people coming here.

112
00:10:11,516 --> 00:10:13,849
You've got lots of men here.
Help me out.

113
00:10:16,057 --> 00:10:17,432
That's difficult for me.

114
00:10:22,766 --> 00:10:24,766
Would this make it better?

115
00:10:25,016 --> 00:10:27,057
What? You want to set me up?

116
00:10:37,599 --> 00:10:38,849
Is that better?

117
00:10:39,682 --> 00:10:42,224
We've already written the report.

118
00:10:42,474 --> 00:10:45,057
That's half a kilo.
Minimum eight to ten years.

119
00:11:02,141 --> 00:11:04,224
Get two of your men
to come back with me.

120
00:11:05,557 --> 00:11:07,016
They're going to say

121
00:11:07,266 --> 00:11:09,932
they saw them take out some drugs.

122
00:11:11,182 --> 00:11:13,849
Being good citizens,
they beat them up.

123
00:11:15,974 --> 00:11:18,807
I'll give them a Good Citizen Award.

124
00:11:19,641 --> 00:11:20,641
How about that?

125
00:11:21,516 --> 00:11:22,474
Good.

126
00:11:23,349 --> 00:11:24,307
Arrest them.

127
00:11:26,307 --> 00:11:27,266
Be polite.

128
00:11:43,724 --> 00:11:45,932
Sir, you can't go in.

129
00:11:49,141 --> 00:11:50,182
Step aside.

130
00:11:52,557 --> 00:11:53,849
Over there.

131
00:11:54,557 --> 00:11:56,266
Yeung Kam Wing,
don't go too far.

132
00:11:56,516 --> 00:11:58,224
I've helped you all these years.

133
00:12:00,724 --> 00:12:01,974
Do you want me dead?

134
00:12:19,432 --> 00:12:21,890
If I go down,
you'll suffer the consequences.

135
00:12:23,057 --> 00:12:25,390
Won't you give me a chance?

136
00:12:39,765 --> 00:12:43,099
ONE MONTH LATER

137
00:13:30,849 --> 00:13:32,349
Delivery from OCTB?

138
00:13:34,599 --> 00:13:39,807
I was transferred from OCTB yesterday
along with the coffee.

139
00:13:40,057 --> 00:13:41,057
Have a seat.

140
00:13:42,307 --> 00:13:43,890
I've given coffee up.

141
00:13:44,140 --> 00:13:47,224
I need sleeping pills
to get to sleep these days.

142
00:13:48,224 --> 00:13:49,890
I can't sleep if I drink coffee.

143
00:13:54,140 --> 00:13:58,349
Life is so unpredictable. I used
to really hate Internal Affairs.

144
00:13:59,057 --> 00:14:01,015
And now, I've been transferred here.

145
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:07,474
You don't seem to be very happy.
I can transfer you elsewhere.

146
00:14:10,140 --> 00:14:11,307
Are you kidding?

147
00:14:11,557 --> 00:14:13,349
I moved here because of you.

148
00:14:14,557 --> 00:14:16,099
The files are on your desk.

149
00:14:17,099 --> 00:14:18,307
The first file...

150
00:14:18,557 --> 00:14:22,057
This sergeant killed himself
in front of his ex-boss, Yeung.

151
00:14:23,599 --> 00:14:26,140
Internal Affairs
is working on a few big cases.

152
00:14:27,557 --> 00:14:30,474
You know Security are very political.

153
00:14:31,182 --> 00:14:33,015
Everything is classified there.

154
00:14:33,307 --> 00:14:36,432
They won't answer
any questions you ask.

155
00:14:36,682 --> 00:14:39,432
We found a letter
on Sergeant Chun's desk.

156
00:14:39,682 --> 00:14:41,515
There was a tape inside.

157
00:14:41,765 --> 00:14:44,349
It was a conversation
between him and Sam.

158
00:14:44,599 --> 00:14:46,890
It turns out he was Sam's mole too.

159
00:14:47,599 --> 00:14:51,557
Besides him, several officers have
also committed suicide or vanished.

160
00:14:51,807 --> 00:14:53,807
They were all Sam's moles.

161
00:14:54,057 --> 00:14:55,890
The bosses say, after Sam's death,

162
00:14:56,140 --> 00:14:59,140
one of the moles is killing
the others to keep his cover.

163
00:14:59,390 --> 00:15:02,474
Leung has ordered us
to find out who he is.

164
00:15:02,724 --> 00:15:04,224
Do you know what happened?

165
00:15:05,182 --> 00:15:08,765
A package was sent to Leung.
Guess what it contained.

166
00:15:11,765 --> 00:15:13,765
It had tapes of us
giving tips to Sam.

167
00:15:15,682 --> 00:15:17,807
Luckily,
Sergeant Chun was one of us.

168
00:15:18,057 --> 00:15:21,182
- How many more of us are there?
- Five, including you.

169
00:15:28,974 --> 00:15:31,140
Ronald, this is Inspector Lau.

170
00:15:32,140 --> 00:15:33,765
I've left something at Admin.

171
00:15:39,682 --> 00:15:41,224
Hello?

172
00:15:41,474 --> 00:15:44,640
I've found out something on Chun.

173
00:15:44,890 --> 00:15:46,640
He was in the Police Bowling Team.

174
00:15:46,890 --> 00:15:47,848
Wait.

175
00:15:48,098 --> 00:15:50,473
- That's what you asked for.
- Good.

176
00:15:50,723 --> 00:15:51,682
Thanks.

177
00:15:52,765 --> 00:15:53,723
Go on.

178
00:15:53,973 --> 00:15:55,890
He practised at the Lam Wah club.

179
00:15:56,140 --> 00:15:58,473
He rented his flat
from Gam Dok Investments,

180
00:15:58,723 --> 00:16:00,473
which owns three big properties.

181
00:16:00,723 --> 00:16:02,807
The owner is Shen, a Mainlander.

182
00:16:03,057 --> 00:16:05,348
I'll e-mail you
the information later.

183
00:16:06,182 --> 00:16:07,557
No, send it to me now.

184
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:17,640
29TH FLOOR, DRAGON VIEW
GARDEN, BROADCAST DRIVE

185
00:16:22,723 --> 00:16:25,848
Inspector Lau, I'm Yeung Kam Wing
from Security Wing.

186
00:16:26,140 --> 00:16:27,848
I applied for a parking space.

187
00:16:28,098 --> 00:16:29,057
Let me check.

188
00:16:29,307 --> 00:16:30,682
I've waited a whole month.

189
00:16:30,932 --> 00:16:33,932
I don't want to bother you,
but will it take much longer?

190
00:16:34,223 --> 00:16:36,807
Sorry, but I've moved back to IA.

191
00:16:39,015 --> 00:16:42,557
I know,
but Admin asked me to contact you.

192
00:16:43,723 --> 00:16:46,682
Your application's
been approved for a month.

193
00:16:46,932 --> 00:16:49,682
Here. Your parking space is B3A6.

194
00:16:50,640 --> 00:16:53,098
We haven't been able
to reach you for a week.

195
00:16:53,348 --> 00:16:55,015
I've been off for a month.

196
00:16:55,265 --> 00:16:57,265
You know IA is investigating me.

197
00:16:57,515 --> 00:17:00,390
- I know.
- Are you investigating Admin today?

198
00:17:01,557 --> 00:17:03,348
No, I'm just picking up a uniform.

199
00:17:04,765 --> 00:17:07,223
That's a sergeant's uniform,
Inspector.

200
00:17:11,932 --> 00:17:14,598
The man who killed himself
in front of you wore it.

201
00:17:14,848 --> 00:17:16,807
I'm taking it back for investigation.

202
00:17:18,182 --> 00:17:19,723
Isn't the case closed now?

203
00:17:19,973 --> 00:17:22,515
Yes, or you wouldn't be back
from your break.

204
00:17:22,765 --> 00:17:24,265
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

205
00:17:24,515 --> 00:17:25,723
B3A6.

206
00:17:34,890 --> 00:17:36,348
Have we met before?

207
00:17:37,015 --> 00:17:37,973
No.

208
00:17:39,515 --> 00:17:42,348
Do you know someone called Shen?

209
00:17:43,848 --> 00:17:44,973
No.

210
00:17:45,223 --> 00:17:47,640
Mind your own business.

211
00:17:50,223 --> 00:17:53,932
We found these photos
inside Chun's bowling locker.

212
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:57,057
That's Shen in the photo.

213
00:17:57,973 --> 00:18:00,223
He used to be Sam's business partner.

214
00:18:00,473 --> 00:18:03,848
The man facing him
is Security Wing's Yeung.

215
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:06,390
He's connected
to the sergeant's death.

216
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:09,223
I think Yeung could be the mole.

217
00:19:19,890 --> 00:19:20,848
Hello?

218
00:19:26,640 --> 00:19:27,598
See you later.

219
00:19:50,890 --> 00:19:54,890
You're a good person. You come
and see him the moment you get back.

220
00:19:58,556 --> 00:19:59,681
You're a good man.

221
00:20:01,348 --> 00:20:05,140
If it wasn't for you,
he wouldn't be buried as a cop.

222
00:20:08,931 --> 00:20:10,306
It was my duty.

223
00:20:13,098 --> 00:20:14,765
I don't know why I helped him.

224
00:20:16,515 --> 00:20:18,765
I only knew him
for about five months.

225
00:20:19,015 --> 00:20:20,473
I've only seen him 21 times.

226
00:20:20,723 --> 00:20:23,348
HE DIED BRAVELY
HIS NOBLE SPIRIT IS ETERNAL

227
00:20:25,056 --> 00:20:26,515
He was a good cop.

228
00:20:28,306 --> 00:20:30,056
Anyone would have helped him.

229
00:20:40,681 --> 00:20:41,890
I'll give you a lift.

230
00:21:04,431 --> 00:21:05,431
Hello.

231
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:08,223
I'm back.

232
00:21:09,181 --> 00:21:10,390
Let's get started.

233
00:21:19,473 --> 00:21:21,973
There are no triads in China.

234
00:21:26,890 --> 00:21:29,223
What China needs is wealth.

235
00:21:30,306 --> 00:21:33,806
Triads are all about life and death.
Business is all about money.

236
00:21:34,056 --> 00:21:36,515
Today, we're here to talk business.

237
00:21:39,390 --> 00:21:42,140
- But I'm a real triad.
- No.

238
00:21:42,931 --> 00:21:46,140
To me, you're the best businessman.

239
00:21:46,973 --> 00:21:48,515
My brother said so too.

240
00:21:49,806 --> 00:21:52,265
We have HK$100 million to spend.

241
00:21:52,515 --> 00:21:54,473
We want to invest in your business.

242
00:21:55,931 --> 00:21:58,140
We'll ask no questions.

243
00:21:58,390 --> 00:22:00,015
It's one country, two systems.

244
00:22:01,015 --> 00:22:05,640
As long as money breeds money,
we'll let you have full control.

245
00:22:06,598 --> 00:22:07,973
You still believe in that?

246
00:22:11,348 --> 00:22:14,515
You won't be able
to refuse our Mainland ties.

247
00:22:14,765 --> 00:22:18,306
You think a Hong Kong triad can
outlive a Mainland businessman?

248
00:22:19,890 --> 00:22:24,181
Without my brother's connections,
your business in China won't last.

249
00:22:30,973 --> 00:22:34,473
Sam, you're a Buddhist, right?

250
00:22:36,265 --> 00:22:37,931
Amitabha.

251
00:22:44,348 --> 00:22:46,848
Is the feng shui good here?

252
00:22:47,098 --> 00:22:49,098
The best in Hong Kong.

253
00:22:50,598 --> 00:22:53,473
I want to get
a longevity tablet here.

254
00:22:55,014 --> 00:22:56,181
For whom?

255
00:22:59,223 --> 00:23:00,348
For my wife.

256
00:23:02,014 --> 00:23:05,181
She died six months ago.

257
00:23:08,139 --> 00:23:10,889
And also one for myself.

258
00:23:14,848 --> 00:23:16,931
That's a small matter,
I'll handle it.

259
00:23:17,639 --> 00:23:19,306
- A small matter?
- Yes.

260
00:23:20,514 --> 00:23:23,473
If it's such a small matter,
let my men deal with it.

261
00:23:24,514 --> 00:23:26,306
We'll see how they handle it.

262
00:23:28,639 --> 00:23:29,681
Goodbye.

263
00:23:30,431 --> 00:23:31,514
Bye.

264
00:23:43,056 --> 00:23:44,348
Keung.

265
00:23:45,681 --> 00:23:47,473
You'll deal with his men.

266
00:23:48,431 --> 00:23:49,889
Are you kidding, Sam?

267
00:23:50,764 --> 00:23:53,306
I'm an idiot.
Do you want it messed up?

268
00:24:01,181 --> 00:24:03,223
What does that laugh mean?

269
00:24:37,723 --> 00:24:39,848
Excuse me. Thank you.

270
00:24:49,806 --> 00:24:50,806
That's a lot.

271
00:24:51,598 --> 00:24:53,014
Are you jealous?

272
00:24:53,264 --> 00:24:55,306
Is it legit? Be careful.

273
00:24:56,473 --> 00:24:58,431
Don't worry, boss.

274
00:24:58,681 --> 00:25:00,806
You know how much money I have.

275
00:25:01,556 --> 00:25:04,639
Just ask if you want a loan.
You don't need to threaten me.

276
00:25:06,889 --> 00:25:09,764
- What's this?
- It's for your baby daughter.

277
00:25:11,389 --> 00:25:13,848
You're a dad now.
You should go home more.

278
00:25:14,098 --> 00:25:15,181
Don't work so hard.

279
00:25:17,806 --> 00:25:20,681
You've lost weight recently.

280
00:25:20,973 --> 00:25:22,973
None of your business. But thanks.

281
00:25:25,889 --> 00:25:27,181
Who are these two?

282
00:25:27,973 --> 00:25:29,723
I only know they're Mainlanders.

283
00:25:29,973 --> 00:25:31,014
Anything else?

284
00:25:37,389 --> 00:25:40,806
Shen was born in Taiyuan, Shanxi.
He's been in the army.

285
00:25:41,056 --> 00:25:44,931
He dealt in antiques. He started
from scratch, now he's loaded.

286
00:25:45,223 --> 00:25:46,806
He came to Hong Kong a year ago.

287
00:25:47,056 --> 00:25:50,806
His brother Liang joined him
and does all the dirty work.

288
00:25:51,056 --> 00:25:53,264
Sam wants to expand to the Mainland.

289
00:25:53,556 --> 00:25:56,306
- What did he want you to talk about?
- Cooperation.

290
00:25:57,389 --> 00:25:58,848
- Liang.
- Yan.

291
00:25:59,098 --> 00:26:00,556
Sit down.

292
00:26:00,806 --> 00:26:01,973
Are you by yourself?

293
00:26:02,223 --> 00:26:03,639
You too, Liang?

294
00:26:06,306 --> 00:26:08,848
We have lots of nightclubs in China.

295
00:26:09,556 --> 00:26:12,514
They're all protected
by local gang bosses.

296
00:26:14,639 --> 00:26:16,639
Influential people.

297
00:26:18,806 --> 00:26:22,597
Your goods can move around
our network easily.

298
00:26:24,556 --> 00:26:27,181
We have businesses in 11 cities.

299
00:26:31,472 --> 00:26:32,431
Excuse me.

300
00:26:35,181 --> 00:26:38,264
- Hello?
- Well, how's the talk so far?

301
00:26:38,514 --> 00:26:39,514
Not bad.

302
00:26:41,431 --> 00:26:43,222
See the ashtray in front of you?

303
00:26:44,514 --> 00:26:47,097
Pick it up and smash him with it.

304
00:26:54,764 --> 00:26:55,806
Hit him!

305
00:26:56,514 --> 00:26:58,514
Hit him in the head!

306
00:27:53,389 --> 00:27:54,972
I'm screwed.

307
00:27:55,222 --> 00:27:57,431
- What is it?
- Mary's pregnant.

308
00:27:58,681 --> 00:28:01,306
- Congratulations.
- But we're not married yet.

309
00:28:01,556 --> 00:28:03,722
- Get married then.
- Is that necessary?

310
00:28:03,972 --> 00:28:06,889
- Or she can have an abortion.
- We're already engaged.

311
00:28:07,139 --> 00:28:08,431
Hello?

312
00:28:08,681 --> 00:28:09,889
Got it.

313
00:28:10,139 --> 00:28:11,764
- We can go.
- Let's go.

314
00:28:16,472 --> 00:28:18,389
Long time no see, Wong.

315
00:28:18,639 --> 00:28:21,722
But I saw you last week
with a girl in China.

316
00:28:21,972 --> 00:28:23,597
You don't have to shout.

317
00:28:23,847 --> 00:28:26,181
Security people are full of secrets.

318
00:28:29,264 --> 00:28:30,306
Stop for a minute.

319
00:28:47,056 --> 00:28:48,847
Hey, what's going on?

320
00:28:49,139 --> 00:28:50,972
What are you doing here?

321
00:28:56,806 --> 00:28:59,847
Hey! What's going on?
What are you doing?

322
00:29:07,639 --> 00:29:08,806
Sorry, sir.

323
00:29:09,056 --> 00:29:12,972
We were asked to take some mugshots.
I don't know what's going on either.

324
00:29:13,806 --> 00:29:15,722
I asked CIB to open a file

325
00:29:16,764 --> 00:29:18,972
and take a picture of everyone.

326
00:29:19,972 --> 00:29:20,931
Is that alright?

327
00:29:24,097 --> 00:29:27,056
Officers, are you done?

328
00:29:28,931 --> 00:29:30,097
Everybody's here.

329
00:29:37,306 --> 00:29:39,681
We were investigating Mr Shen...

330
00:29:41,139 --> 00:29:44,305
...but we ended up
being led to Sam by chance.

331
00:29:45,097 --> 00:29:46,555
We even arrested Sam's men.

332
00:29:47,472 --> 00:29:49,639
I'll let CIB handle the triads.

333
00:29:49,889 --> 00:29:51,597
Sam, long time no see. Are you OK?

334
00:29:52,639 --> 00:29:56,597
- What brings you here?
- I'm accompanying some friends.

335
00:29:59,180 --> 00:30:01,805
You Hong Kong Police
are so inefficient.

336
00:30:03,097 --> 00:30:04,555
I'll speed it up then.

337
00:30:05,597 --> 00:30:07,764
He beat you up.

338
00:30:08,014 --> 00:30:09,555
Do you want to press charges?

339
00:30:09,847 --> 00:30:11,930
If not, then please sign here.

340
00:30:44,222 --> 00:30:46,055
I hit you. Want to press charges?

341
00:30:46,347 --> 00:30:47,514
You're crazy.

342
00:30:51,097 --> 00:30:53,222
Keung, let's go.

343
00:30:54,139 --> 00:30:55,097
Wait.

344
00:31:09,722 --> 00:31:11,347
Do you recognise me?

345
00:31:15,264 --> 00:31:18,014
I recognise you. Be careful.

346
00:31:23,097 --> 00:31:24,722
Wong.

347
00:31:25,555 --> 00:31:27,972
It's up to you what you do with them.

348
00:31:32,889 --> 00:31:34,555
It's OK. We all know each other.

349
00:31:47,930 --> 00:31:50,264
CIB colleagues, you can go now.

350
00:31:50,514 --> 00:31:52,097
Thanks, Ming. Thank you.

351
00:31:52,347 --> 00:31:53,805
Just doing my job.

352
00:31:54,055 --> 00:31:55,472
Let's go.

353
00:32:00,639 --> 00:32:01,639
What's your game?

354
00:32:03,347 --> 00:32:06,055
You think I'm playing?
It's life and death.

355
00:32:06,347 --> 00:32:07,472
I'm glad you know that.

356
00:32:25,597 --> 00:32:26,930
Hurry up and thank me.

357
00:32:27,180 --> 00:32:28,514
Thank you for what?

358
00:32:28,764 --> 00:32:31,347
- Look what you're doing.
- Eating.

359
00:32:31,597 --> 00:32:33,305
You're eating shark fin.

360
00:32:33,555 --> 00:32:35,264
Shark fin, think about it.

361
00:32:35,514 --> 00:32:39,389
When Sam took me to Thailand,
I had shark fin and then I moved up.

362
00:32:40,180 --> 00:32:42,764
You're having shark fin
so you're moving up.

363
00:32:43,014 --> 00:32:46,139
Sam's mean,
but he still bought you shark fin.

364
00:32:46,389 --> 00:32:47,680
Just think about it.

365
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:06,639
Take him.

366
00:33:09,055 --> 00:33:10,097
Let go of him.

367
00:33:15,138 --> 00:33:16,222
Sam,

368
00:33:17,305 --> 00:33:19,513
are you letting them
take Yan to China?

369
00:33:20,972 --> 00:33:22,638
Ask him why he smashed his head.

370
00:33:28,138 --> 00:33:29,888
He smashed his head?

371
00:33:30,138 --> 00:33:31,097
That's nothing.

372
00:33:31,347 --> 00:33:34,013
In this job,
either you get them or they get you.

373
00:33:35,180 --> 00:33:38,888
Yan smashed his head, right?
How about this?

374
00:33:42,097 --> 00:33:43,680
Is that alright now?

375
00:33:52,930 --> 00:33:53,888
Liang.

376
00:33:59,013 --> 00:34:01,638
Are you here to make a scene...

377
00:34:02,930 --> 00:34:05,180
...or are you here for business?

378
00:34:11,305 --> 00:34:12,263
Go.

379
00:34:13,305 --> 00:34:14,263
Go!

380
00:34:21,222 --> 00:34:22,513
We're even now.

381
00:34:23,430 --> 00:34:24,972
Let's talk business.

382
00:34:28,472 --> 00:34:30,430
I heard
you have a big arms business.

383
00:34:30,722 --> 00:34:32,847
If you let me chip in...

384
00:34:35,555 --> 00:34:38,555
...the blood they have spilt
will not be in vain.

385
00:34:52,680 --> 00:34:53,847
Sam.

386
00:35:02,305 --> 00:35:03,347
So?

387
00:35:04,763 --> 00:35:06,097
You're not happy with me?

388
00:35:07,513 --> 00:35:08,472
No.

389
00:35:12,805 --> 00:35:14,305
Have you ever met someone...

390
00:35:15,763 --> 00:35:17,180
...who seems nice...

391
00:35:18,972 --> 00:35:20,847
...but who might kill you at any time?

392
00:35:25,055 --> 00:35:26,472
I've met someone like that.

393
00:35:31,097 --> 00:35:32,513
What do you think, Sam?

394
00:35:36,180 --> 00:35:37,555
I'm wondering...

395
00:35:39,388 --> 00:35:40,680
...why he didn't kill you.

396
00:35:45,222 --> 00:35:48,097
You'll look after
the Mainland business from now on.

397
00:35:51,138 --> 00:35:52,763
Take this for now.

398
00:36:09,972 --> 00:36:11,347
Shen's not what he seems.

399
00:36:11,597 --> 00:36:13,305
Security is investigating him.

400
00:36:14,305 --> 00:36:16,555
He could be smuggling arms.

401
00:36:16,805 --> 00:36:18,805
Sam stopped all his deals in China.

402
00:36:19,055 --> 00:36:21,013
They're going to work together soon.

403
00:36:21,263 --> 00:36:22,847
That's a big deal.

404
00:36:25,055 --> 00:36:26,472
What should I do?

405
00:36:27,222 --> 00:36:28,513
Have you seen the shrink?

406
00:36:29,347 --> 00:36:31,347
Why should I see a shrink?

407
00:36:31,597 --> 00:36:34,930
I persuaded the Department
of Justice not to send you to prison.

408
00:36:35,180 --> 00:36:39,722
It's fine if you don't want to go.
See you in prison. Bye.

409
00:36:40,930 --> 00:36:43,388
Hello? Hello? What's the address?

410
00:36:45,055 --> 00:36:46,013
Bye.

411
00:36:47,721 --> 00:36:49,305
I'm meeting with Dr Lee.

412
00:36:49,555 --> 00:36:50,513
This way.

413
00:38:04,055 --> 00:38:06,888
Are you planning
to spend the night here?

414
00:38:11,805 --> 00:38:13,680
I can't fall asleep in my office.

415
00:38:18,180 --> 00:38:19,221
Unlike him.

416
00:38:33,638 --> 00:38:35,263
He said...

417
00:38:36,930 --> 00:38:38,638
...ever since he became a mole...

418
00:38:42,471 --> 00:38:44,763
...he could only fall asleep here.

419
00:38:57,846 --> 00:38:59,013
I still remember...

420
00:39:01,930 --> 00:39:02,930
That night...

421
00:39:06,388 --> 00:39:08,930
He said everything
would be OK after tomorrow.

422
00:39:13,638 --> 00:39:15,471
And then he died.

423
00:39:36,221 --> 00:39:37,430
You're a doctor.

424
00:39:45,596 --> 00:39:48,555
Do you still have his file?

425
00:39:51,180 --> 00:39:54,513
He may be dead,
but he's still a patient.

426
00:40:00,305 --> 00:40:01,471
- Let's go.
- OK.

427
00:40:14,013 --> 00:40:17,096
THREE HOURS LATER

428
00:41:10,638 --> 00:41:14,554
We found a letter on Sergeant Chun's
desk. There was a tape inside.

429
00:41:14,804 --> 00:41:17,804
It was a conversation
between him and Sam.

430
00:41:18,471 --> 00:41:20,263
The bosses say, after Sam's death,

431
00:41:20,554 --> 00:41:23,471
one of the moles is killing
the others to keep his cover.

432
00:41:24,513 --> 00:41:26,554
He's connected to Chun's death.

433
00:41:27,429 --> 00:41:29,596
I think Yeung could be the mole.

434
00:43:45,929 --> 00:43:48,262
Do you understand what I said?

435
00:43:48,512 --> 00:43:49,471
Sorry.

436
00:43:50,637 --> 00:43:54,304
I won't sign it
if she doesn't come and meet me.

437
00:43:54,554 --> 00:43:55,554
Do you understand?

438
00:43:56,596 --> 00:43:57,554
OK.

439
00:44:14,429 --> 00:44:16,471
My wife and I
may be getting divorced.

440
00:44:18,096 --> 00:44:19,179
Did I scare you?

441
00:44:20,262 --> 00:44:21,221
Sorry.

442
00:44:22,054 --> 00:44:23,012
Be careful.

443
00:44:23,304 --> 00:44:24,387
Of what?

444
00:44:25,971 --> 00:44:28,929
Your car's next to mine.
I drive badly.

445
00:44:29,179 --> 00:44:31,721
If I scratch your car,
come and find me.

446
00:44:36,512 --> 00:44:38,971
I'm a good driver.
You don't have to worry.

447
00:45:27,596 --> 00:45:30,762
The Taiwanese we arrested
will be discharged next week.

448
00:45:31,012 --> 00:45:33,179
The Taiwan authorities
have no comment.

449
00:45:33,429 --> 00:45:36,262
The Mainland police
will come for extradition.

450
00:45:36,512 --> 00:45:38,221
I know their boss well.

451
00:45:38,471 --> 00:45:40,887
Stick to the plan and be careful.

452
00:45:41,137 --> 00:45:42,596
When they arrive,

453
00:45:42,846 --> 00:45:46,429
make them feel welcome and take
them out for dinner and shopping.

454
00:45:47,096 --> 00:45:48,971
How about a nightclub?

455
00:45:49,221 --> 00:45:50,596
Macau is better.

456
00:45:50,846 --> 00:45:52,762
You're not afraid of reporters?

457
00:45:53,012 --> 00:45:55,512
We can cover their heads with bags.

458
00:45:55,762 --> 00:45:58,596
- OK, you bring the bags.
- What are you like?

459
00:45:59,721 --> 00:46:01,179
Superintendent Yeung.

460
00:46:01,429 --> 00:46:04,012
It's Sergeant Chun's memorial
next week.

461
00:46:04,262 --> 00:46:06,387
We're all chipping in for a service.

462
00:46:23,429 --> 00:46:25,179
- Do it properly.
- Yes, sir.

463
00:46:25,429 --> 00:46:28,762
Back to the Mainland police.
Talk to the Macau guys tomorrow.

464
00:46:29,012 --> 00:46:32,971
Let them plan the evening.
I'll talk to them about security.

465
00:46:33,637 --> 00:46:37,012
If we don't plan, it'll be a mess.
Then we won't have a good time.

466
00:51:52,678 --> 00:51:54,595
Anything to add to your testimony?

467
00:51:56,345 --> 00:51:57,303
No.

468
00:51:58,303 --> 00:52:00,803
Call us any time
if you need anything.

469
00:52:01,387 --> 00:52:02,470
Thank you.

470
00:52:03,970 --> 00:52:05,387
- Are you done?
- Yes.

471
00:52:08,012 --> 00:52:10,470
- Is it OK if I touch things?
- Yes.

472
00:52:10,720 --> 00:52:11,845
OK, thank you.

473
00:52:16,262 --> 00:52:18,220
Is everything OK?

474
00:52:19,470 --> 00:52:21,095
It was like this when I came in.

475
00:52:22,970 --> 00:52:26,012
They stole some cash and watches.

476
00:52:27,345 --> 00:52:28,845
And the computer's gone.

477
00:52:31,928 --> 00:52:35,762
It's better this way.
I can start from scratch.

478
00:52:39,553 --> 00:52:41,428
But the computer's useless to them.

479
00:52:44,095 --> 00:52:45,928
I locked it with my password.

480
00:52:46,678 --> 00:52:49,387
They won't know
it's my license plate number.

481
00:52:58,887 --> 00:53:01,345
Your eyes are all red.

482
00:53:02,137 --> 00:53:03,678
You haven't slept?

483
00:53:05,470 --> 00:53:08,095
I've been
following several cases for days.

484
00:53:09,512 --> 00:53:10,887
You should get some sleep.

485
00:53:16,470 --> 00:53:19,262
OK.
Everything will be OK after tomorrow.

486
00:53:21,012 --> 00:53:23,220
I'm off.
Call me if you need anything.

487
00:54:11,012 --> 00:54:11,970
Mr Chan.

488
00:54:13,345 --> 00:54:18,428
AUGUST 16TH 2002
THE FIRST SESSION

489
00:54:21,011 --> 00:54:23,470
Mr Chan, I'm Dr Lee.

490
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:28,553
I'm obligated to tell you that you've
been ordered to undergo treatment.

491
00:54:29,470 --> 00:54:32,428
You should complete the treatment
in six months.

492
00:54:33,761 --> 00:54:36,761
After that,
I'll submit a report to the Court.

493
00:54:38,303 --> 00:54:41,178
The Court will use that
to decide if you should go to prison.

494
00:54:44,845 --> 00:54:45,803
Prison?

495
00:54:47,136 --> 00:54:48,636
Isn't the treatment enough?

496
00:54:49,345 --> 00:54:52,345
You must follow
doctor's orders during this time

497
00:54:52,595 --> 00:54:55,636
or the Court can revoke the sentence

498
00:54:55,886 --> 00:54:58,511
and detain you for handling.

499
00:54:58,761 --> 00:54:59,803
I see.

500
00:55:03,178 --> 00:55:04,636
Excuse me.

501
00:55:09,386 --> 00:55:11,095
Wong, you git.

502
00:55:14,720 --> 00:55:18,011
Dr Lee, you don't need
to call the police. Just call me.

503
00:55:18,261 --> 00:55:19,636
You have my mobile number.

504
00:55:25,220 --> 00:55:26,970
I'll become a wanted criminal.

505
00:55:27,220 --> 00:55:30,553
THE SECOND SESSION

506
00:55:36,595 --> 00:55:38,928
Mr Chan, I'm Dr Lee.

507
00:55:39,178 --> 00:55:43,470
I'm obligated to tell you that you've
been ordered to undergo treatment.

508
00:55:43,720 --> 00:55:46,553
You should complete the treatment
in six months.

509
00:55:46,803 --> 00:55:48,803
You'll submit a report to the Court.

510
00:55:49,053 --> 00:55:52,928
They'll use this report and they
might put me in prison. I get it.

511
00:55:53,928 --> 00:55:55,595
Please sign here then.

512
00:55:59,595 --> 00:56:01,803
We think you have a violent streak

513
00:56:02,095 --> 00:56:04,595
so we'll use hypnotism
for your treatment.

514
00:56:04,886 --> 00:56:05,636
Hypnotism?

515
00:56:07,636 --> 00:56:08,678
You signed the form.

516
00:56:09,386 --> 00:56:10,345
Hypnotism?

517
00:56:13,636 --> 00:56:15,053
You can refuse it

518
00:56:15,303 --> 00:56:17,095
but the Court can revoke it.

519
00:56:17,386 --> 00:56:18,886
And lock me up?

520
00:56:25,011 --> 00:56:26,178
Alright, then.

521
00:56:27,970 --> 00:56:28,928
Hypnotize me.

522
00:56:29,761 --> 00:56:31,178
Hypnotize me now.

523
00:56:33,178 --> 00:56:34,303
Let's begin.

524
00:56:35,678 --> 00:56:37,511
Please introduce yourself.

525
00:56:37,761 --> 00:56:39,345
Talk about your family.

526
00:56:43,886 --> 00:56:44,845
Mr Chan?

527
00:56:46,011 --> 00:56:46,970
Mr Chan.

528
00:56:48,970 --> 00:56:50,136
Can you cooperate?

