01:24:36,134 --> 01:24:37,634
If anything goes wrong...

801
01:24:37,884 --> 01:24:39,175
I know.

802
01:24:39,759 --> 01:24:41,675
You go with me to the dockyard.

803
01:24:50,384 --> 01:24:53,009
Shen and Sam's deal
is happening tonight.

804
01:24:53,259 --> 01:24:56,342
They might be heavily armed.
Wear bulletproof vests.

805
01:24:57,134 --> 01:24:58,925
The water police are standing by.

806
01:24:59,217 --> 01:25:01,384
Teams A and B,
get ready on the hill.

807
01:25:03,509 --> 01:25:04,759
Call the operation off.

808
01:25:06,300 --> 01:25:07,550
What are you saying?

809
01:25:08,259 --> 01:25:09,634
It's an order from the top.

810
01:25:16,509 --> 01:25:18,217
An order from the top or from you?

811
01:25:19,925 --> 01:25:21,175
I don't need to explain.

812
01:25:23,842 --> 01:25:27,217
I've been on Sam's trail for years.
What are your ties with him?

813
01:25:28,384 --> 01:25:30,175
This is Security's top secret.

814
01:25:30,425 --> 01:25:33,759
You can make a formal inquiry
to the Assistant Commissioner.

815
01:25:35,467 --> 01:25:37,425
- Call IA and check.
- Yes, sir.

816
01:25:48,175 --> 01:25:50,258
Just do what Yeung says.

817
01:25:50,508 --> 01:25:51,467
I won't.

818
01:25:51,717 --> 01:25:54,592
Wong,
this isn't as simple as you think.

819
01:25:54,842 --> 01:25:56,508
It's very simple for me, sir.

820
01:25:56,758 --> 01:25:58,633
My man is risking his life out there.

821
01:25:59,592 --> 01:26:03,758
Everybody in OCTB stays put. You're
under disciplinary investigation.

822
01:26:06,717 --> 01:26:08,217
What disciplinary issues?

823
01:26:09,133 --> 01:26:12,133
You don't follow orders.
That's a disciplinary issue.

824
01:26:19,217 --> 01:26:20,342
Where are you going?

825
01:26:22,008 --> 01:26:23,508
Back to my office, sir.

826
01:26:27,467 --> 01:26:29,008
You can go.

827
01:26:43,425 --> 01:26:45,050
- Tang.
- Yes.

828
01:26:45,300 --> 01:26:47,050
- Turn back.
- OK.

829
01:26:47,300 --> 01:26:49,008
Ask everyone to follow our car.

830
01:26:51,258 --> 01:26:54,717
Sam, Yan's doing the transaction.

831
01:28:15,842 --> 01:28:16,800
Hello?

832
01:28:17,050 --> 01:28:20,258
Your wife has agreed to meet you
this afternoon. Is that OK?

833
01:28:23,467 --> 01:28:25,133
Thank you. Thank you.

834
01:28:31,717 --> 01:28:34,800
The Mainlanders
will come in today for extradition.

835
01:28:35,050 --> 01:28:37,800
Make sure nothing goes wrong.
Be careful.

836
01:28:38,050 --> 01:28:41,050
- Damon and Fai, you stay here.
- OK.

837
01:28:41,592 --> 01:28:44,258
Set the channel to 34879. OK?

838
01:28:45,050 --> 01:28:47,550
- Tell Transportation we can go now.
- OK.

839
01:29:27,091 --> 01:29:28,050
Thank you.

840
01:30:55,883 --> 01:30:58,633
Inspector Lau,
are you having fun in my office?

841
01:32:18,925 --> 01:32:21,341
Everybody, get ready. Follow me.

842
01:32:23,300 --> 01:32:24,300
What's going on?

843
01:32:24,550 --> 01:32:26,508
We're having Yeung round for coffee.

844
01:32:30,383 --> 01:32:34,425
The Mainlanders are chatting inside.
They'll meet our boss in 15 minutes.

845
01:32:34,675 --> 01:32:36,216
Don't make any mistakes.

846
01:32:36,466 --> 01:32:38,633
Damon and Fai,
get the documents ready.

847
01:32:48,174 --> 01:32:49,299
Yeung Kam Wing.

848
01:32:50,299 --> 01:32:52,591
You're suspected
of conspiring with Sam.

849
01:32:52,841 --> 01:32:54,883
Please come back with us to IA.

850
01:32:57,299 --> 01:33:00,341
Inspector Lau,
do you know what you're doing?

851
01:33:00,633 --> 01:33:01,633
I know.

852
01:33:06,258 --> 01:33:07,383
I found a tape.

853
01:33:08,091 --> 01:33:09,966
What tape? I don't understand.

854
01:33:11,091 --> 01:33:12,549
Listen and you will.

855
01:33:40,091 --> 01:33:41,174
Where's Sam?

856
01:33:41,799 --> 01:33:43,049
Sam's not here yet?

857
01:34:04,716 --> 01:34:05,799
They're empty!

858
01:34:07,716 --> 01:34:08,674
Shen!

859
01:34:49,133 --> 01:34:51,674
The arms cost HK$10 million.
Give them back.

860
01:34:51,924 --> 01:34:53,633
Those Mainlanders are animals.

861
01:34:55,133 --> 01:34:57,966
- What if they're setting me up?
- Who told you that?

862
01:34:59,924 --> 01:35:01,383
My life told me so.

863
01:35:02,091 --> 01:35:03,424
What if you're wrong?

864
01:35:04,674 --> 01:35:07,008
Then I'll cooperate with them.

865
01:35:08,674 --> 01:35:10,716
But Yan's going to die either way?

866
01:35:12,383 --> 01:35:15,549
We're all risking our lives
in this business.

867
01:35:16,841 --> 01:35:18,341
I almost died twice.

868
01:35:19,216 --> 01:35:20,799
Sam, don't play games.

869
01:35:21,299 --> 01:35:22,591
Sam!

870
01:35:22,841 --> 01:35:25,008
I've only ever had one guy
work for me!

871
01:35:25,258 --> 01:35:27,299
How can you do this to me?

872
01:35:28,424 --> 01:35:29,924
What are you saying?

873
01:36:10,007 --> 01:36:11,049
Tell me.

874
01:36:13,257 --> 01:36:14,216
Tell me.

875
01:36:15,591 --> 01:36:16,841
Where are my goods?

876
01:36:17,507 --> 01:36:18,924
Where have you put them?

877
01:36:20,466 --> 01:36:21,841
Go and ask Sam yourself.

878
01:36:31,257 --> 01:36:35,007
Why didn't you shoot me in the head?

879
01:36:37,132 --> 01:36:38,091
I didn't aim.

880
01:36:38,382 --> 01:36:39,549
Stand up.

881
01:36:40,507 --> 01:36:41,841
Stand up!

882
01:36:53,424 --> 01:36:55,174
Are you two in this together?

883
01:36:58,341 --> 01:37:00,132
You two are in this together.

884
01:37:00,674 --> 01:37:02,716
Sorry, I'm a cop.

885
01:37:03,466 --> 01:37:04,799
Go ahead and shoot.

886
01:37:05,091 --> 01:37:06,716
It'll save me a bullet.

887
01:37:08,382 --> 01:37:10,841
What? Are you sure you're a cop?

888
01:37:11,674 --> 01:37:15,132
I am.
I got an "A" for writing reports.

889
01:37:15,924 --> 01:37:19,049
After I kill both of you,
I can write what I like.

890
01:37:37,174 --> 01:37:39,007
He's not really Sam's man.

891
01:37:48,632 --> 01:37:50,507
Then you're not really Shen.

892
01:38:07,132 --> 01:38:08,632
You're just in time.

893
01:38:09,674 --> 01:38:11,924
Listen with us. It's interesting.

894
01:38:18,882 --> 01:38:22,049
So you don't want to help me,
Inspector Lau?

895
01:38:22,299 --> 01:38:24,841
I do, but they're watching me.

896
01:38:25,091 --> 01:38:28,966
So you're not worried about me.
You're worried about yourself.

897
01:38:29,216 --> 01:38:30,632
Whatever you say.

898
01:38:32,466 --> 01:38:33,716
You deal with him.

899
01:38:35,341 --> 01:38:38,216
Give me three days.
I'll run a check and call you.

900
01:38:51,632 --> 01:38:52,632
Inspector Lau.

901
01:38:54,591 --> 01:38:58,466
Lau Kin Ming,
this is your last chance.

902
01:38:59,799 --> 01:39:01,132
Don't waste it.

903
01:39:08,466 --> 01:39:11,132
Lau Kin Ming, you're under arrest.

904
01:39:11,382 --> 01:39:15,007
Lau Kin Ming's over there! What are
you doing? What are you doing?

905
01:39:15,966 --> 01:39:19,174
We agreed to arrest him.
Why are you helping him?

906
01:39:19,424 --> 01:39:21,507
Yeung found this tape in your room.

907
01:39:21,757 --> 01:39:25,757
- What's the problem?
- That cop was following me.

908
01:39:26,632 --> 01:39:29,549
I'm in charge now.
Call me if you've got transactions.

909
01:39:29,799 --> 01:39:31,882
We got the goods
when we killed the cop.

910
01:39:32,674 --> 01:39:33,841
Cuff him.

911
01:39:34,632 --> 01:39:35,632
What are you doing?

912
01:39:35,924 --> 01:39:37,715
Move back! Sit down!

913
01:39:38,007 --> 01:39:39,507
Sit down! Move back!

914
01:39:39,799 --> 01:39:41,590
- Inspector Lau...
- Move back!

915
01:39:42,299 --> 01:39:43,590
Move back!

916
01:39:43,840 --> 01:39:44,965
What are you doing?

917
01:39:50,049 --> 01:39:51,340
I told you to be careful.

918
01:39:51,632 --> 01:39:52,882
Why should I be careful?

919
01:39:53,132 --> 01:39:55,799
Why? I'm a good man.
Why should I be careful?

920
01:39:56,090 --> 01:39:57,299
Why?

921
01:40:03,132 --> 01:40:04,465
I worked so hard.

922
01:40:06,299 --> 01:40:07,465
I helped you kill...

923
01:40:08,757 --> 01:40:10,007
...all of Sam's moles.

924
01:40:10,257 --> 01:40:14,840
Why can't you give me a chance?
Why can't you give me a chance?

925
01:40:15,090 --> 01:40:16,507
I only want to be a good man.

926
01:40:17,465 --> 01:40:18,840
I only want to be a good man.

927
01:40:19,799 --> 01:40:21,924
Why can't
you give me a chance? Why?

928
01:40:22,215 --> 01:40:24,132
Tell me!

929
01:40:25,340 --> 01:40:27,507
Sorry, I'm a cop.

930
01:40:34,924 --> 01:40:37,632
Sorry, I'm a cop.

931
01:40:39,299 --> 01:40:40,382
I'm a cop too!

932
01:41:40,965 --> 01:41:44,007
Are you sure
you won't go to the hospital?

933
01:41:45,340 --> 01:41:48,174
People like me can't go out
into the light.

934
01:41:49,590 --> 01:41:50,590
Same here.

935
01:41:51,465 --> 01:41:54,757
I'll get more credits if I bleed.
Did I cause you trouble?

936
01:41:55,049 --> 01:41:56,590
It's just a report.

937
01:41:58,132 --> 01:42:01,090
- Be careful when dealing with Sam.
- You too.

938
01:42:02,465 --> 01:42:04,049
It was Sam who set you up.

939
01:42:04,299 --> 01:42:06,465
You won't bump into me next time.

940
01:42:08,340 --> 01:42:10,674
Will we see each other again?

941
01:42:11,340 --> 01:42:13,882
- I'll pass.
- Speak Mandarin.

942
01:42:14,132 --> 01:42:16,465
I'm going to Beijing next week.
Come along.

943
01:42:17,549 --> 01:42:18,924
I'll quit after this.

944
01:42:21,507 --> 01:42:22,465
And you?

945
01:42:23,382 --> 01:42:25,382
I'm a mole,

946
01:42:26,132 --> 01:42:27,465
we don't have holidays.

947
01:42:30,174 --> 01:42:31,174
OK.

948
01:42:32,674 --> 01:42:35,090
See you. See you.

949
01:42:35,340 --> 01:42:38,674
You haven't told us yet.
What's your name?

950
01:42:41,090 --> 01:42:42,132
Name?

951
01:42:42,882 --> 01:42:43,965
I don't know.

952
01:42:44,215 --> 01:42:46,174
Just call me Shadow.

953
01:42:46,965 --> 01:42:48,299
That's so corny!

954
01:42:51,424 --> 01:42:52,674
It's time for me to go.

955
01:42:53,674 --> 01:42:57,215
You haven't answered me yet.
I asked you if you recognised me.

956
01:42:59,257 --> 01:43:01,132
At the cadet school in 1991,

957
01:43:01,382 --> 01:43:04,049
if you hadn't left,
I wouldn't have got the Award.

958
01:44:29,298 --> 01:44:32,673
Lau's been taken to the hospital.
He's still in critical condition.

959
01:44:32,882 --> 01:44:35,465
The bullet is in his brain.

960
01:44:36,173 --> 01:44:38,382
The doctors
say that even if he recovers,

961
01:44:38,632 --> 01:44:40,632
his brain will be severely damaged.

962
01:44:40,882 --> 01:44:43,632
His room is full
of information about the moles.

963
01:44:43,882 --> 01:44:46,798
The department
was covered by hidden cameras

964
01:44:47,048 --> 01:44:49,340
that were connected
to Yeung's computer.

965
01:45:13,840 --> 01:45:14,798
Hello?

966
01:45:17,632 --> 01:45:18,715
Mary?

967
01:45:20,132 --> 01:45:21,965
He won't be able to meet you.

968
01:45:48,215 --> 01:45:53,090
DECEMBER 2002
TEN DAYS AFTER YAN'S DEATH

969
01:46:05,173 --> 01:46:06,840
He's dead.

970
01:46:07,632 --> 01:46:09,298
What's the point?

971
01:46:13,923 --> 01:46:17,257
There are things we've got to do.

972
01:46:55,298 --> 01:46:57,465
Hey, you're right.

973
01:47:53,215 --> 01:47:54,590
Dr Lee,

974
01:47:55,465 --> 01:47:57,298
everything will be OK after today.

975
01:47:58,256 --> 01:48:01,256
I'll arrest Lau Kin Ming myself.

976
01:48:12,590 --> 01:48:15,840
ONE MONTH LATER

977
01:48:33,423 --> 01:48:35,048
I'm giving it back to you.

978
01:48:38,965 --> 01:48:40,715
He turned me into a cripple.

979
01:49:12,756 --> 01:49:14,465
Was he Yan's friend?

980
01:49:21,131 --> 01:49:24,048
They were in cadet school together.

981
01:49:28,465 --> 01:49:31,756
12 YEARS EARLIER

982
01:49:32,256 --> 01:49:35,131
You have to follow the rules
at cadet school.

983
01:49:35,381 --> 01:49:39,256
Those who break the rules will be
like him. They'll be expelled.

984
01:49:40,298 --> 01:49:42,590
Who wants to trade places with him?

985
01:49:46,465 --> 01:49:49,465
Yeung, congratulations
on getting the Award.

986
01:49:50,215 --> 01:49:52,840
Would he have got it
if he hadn't been expelled?

987
01:50:12,881 --> 01:50:14,381
Perhaps that's fate.

988
01:50:15,589 --> 01:50:18,423
Destiny is destiny.

989
01:50:20,131 --> 01:50:24,131
Men are changed by events,
not events by men.

990
01:50:27,339 --> 01:50:28,464
But these two men...

991
01:50:30,256 --> 01:50:32,214
...they have changed certain events.

992
01:50:37,589 --> 01:50:38,548
OK...

993
01:50:40,089 --> 01:50:41,798
Let bygones be bygones.

994
01:50:44,173 --> 01:50:46,006
Tomorrow is another day.

995
01:50:50,589 --> 01:50:51,589
Bye.

996
01:51:24,089 --> 01:51:28,714
SEVEN MONTHS LATER

997
01:51:59,464 --> 01:52:00,881
You're here?

998
01:52:30,673 --> 01:52:32,256
The baby can say "daddy" now.

999
01:53:03,798 --> 01:53:06,381
He shot me so I shot him back,
like a triad would.

1000
01:53:06,631 --> 01:53:09,006
NOVEMBER 2002
A WEEK BEFORE YAN'S DEATH

1001
01:53:09,256 --> 01:53:12,256
Stop having a go at me
and learn from Yeung.

1002
01:53:12,506 --> 01:53:13,506
Learn what?

1003
01:53:13,756 --> 01:53:15,548
Learn how to write a report.

1004
01:53:15,798 --> 01:53:18,089
If you've killed someone,
it's a big deal.

1005
01:53:18,339 --> 01:53:19,756
So it's OK if I got killed?

1006
01:53:21,006 --> 01:53:22,381
Send me a report.

1007
01:53:22,631 --> 01:53:24,214
I'll send you nothing.

1008
01:53:24,923 --> 01:53:26,089
What did you say?

1009
01:53:35,798 --> 01:53:37,631
- You can go.
- What?

1010
01:53:37,881 --> 01:53:40,089
- Lunchtime.
- I've just had breakfast.

1011
01:53:40,339 --> 01:53:43,172
Would you rather eat shit instead?

1012
01:53:52,881 --> 01:53:54,256
Excuse me.

1013
01:53:54,547 --> 01:53:55,839
What is it?

1014
01:53:57,672 --> 01:54:00,297
I'd like to try this stereo.

1015
01:54:12,214 --> 01:54:14,631
KSITIGARBHA SUTRA:

1016
01:54:14,881 --> 01:54:18,756
SUCH PEOPLE SHALL BE CAST
INTO THE NEVER-ENDING HELL

1017
01:54:19,006 --> 01:54:22,881
AND WILL SUFFER CONTINUOUSLY
FOREVER AND EVER

1018
01:54:23,131 --> 01:54:26,089
WITH NO MEANS OF ESCAPE.


